{"id": "EUVD-2024-2356", "enisaUuid": "fc485891-1793-3127-ab1e-68cf7a487041", "description": "Apache NiFi 1.10.0 through 1.26.0 and 2.0.0-M1 through 2.0.0-M3 support a description field in the Parameter Context configuration that is vulnerable to cross-site scripting. An authenticated user, authorized to configure a Parameter Context, can enter arbitrary JavaScript code, which the client browser will execute within the session context of the authenticated user. Upgrading to Apache NiFi 1.27.0 or 2.0.0-M4 is the recommended mitigation.", "datePublished": "2024-07-08T07:29:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-09-13T17:04:52", "baseScore": 4.6, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:R/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-37389", "https://github.com/apache/nifi/pull/8938", "https://github.com/apache/nifi/commit/1ea0bc1f7fa90ecff0ceb8b0c91a9aebeb05893b", "https://github.com/apache/nifi", "https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NIFI-13374", "https://lists.apache.org/thread/yso9fr0wtff53nk046h1o83hdyb1lrxh"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-37389", "GHSA-h658-qqv9-qwv8"], "assigner": "apache", "epss": 0.95, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "a71123d7-1b38-33db-91f6-3f6dca09790c", "product": {"name": "Apache NiFi"}, "product_version": "2.0.0-M1 \u22642.0.0-M3"}, {"id": "c02c4549-b690-3c2a-a372-de7ca4c06423", "product": {"name": "Apache NiFi"}, "product_version": "1.10.0 \u22641.26.0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "89af5704-f0c3-3f3c-bf7c-b10da702c389", "vendor": {"name": "Apache Software Foundation"}}], "isExploited": false}